I don’t like to share. That’s a general theme in my life that’s been exposed a lot lately. It’s embarrassing but refining and necessary.

When we were baking, I was brainstorming excuses that I could give the kids so that I could ice the cookies in peace by myself. It’s been a long time since we’ve baked anything nice and I just wanted them to look nice and it’s SO therapeutic for me to ice them. But how would they ever forgive me…

So I sucked it up and compromised and let them ice and decorate to their hearts’ content. We all had a great time and here are some of the nicer ones.

It’s these little moments throughout the day that confront me to refine my character. My flaws have never been more apparent since becoming a mother but I’ve never been so eager to work at being better .. because little eyes are always watching 👀 #thankfulmama

No regrets!.. except maybe it’d be nicer to look more presentable every day as a career woman 💄.. or maybe not because I remember that gets old fast 🤣

It’s easy to waver and doubt the decision to stay home. It is absolutely an undervalued and even shamed role when it deserves to be celebrated.

What gives me confidence with my decision? 👉👉 That it was an intentional decision that was carefully thought out and prayed over with my husband. 
It wasn’t that I got lazy, or that we made enough money so I didn’t need to work, or that I got too attached to my babies, or anything of the sort.

Rather, I went in knowing my purpose, my motive and my hope. 👉👉 I want to be able to serve my family and home fully and shepherd & teach my children in the Lord without distraction.

So when the days are difficult and I’m feeling exasperated or insecure, I can look back at my original intent and that makes me press on with joy. 
.
.
.

Look at us. We’re just a young couple; fresh and maybe a little green, and trying to raise our growing family. The prospect of retirement seems distant, not to mention retirement planning can feel like a daunting ordeal. That’s why we are planning early, talking about OUR retirement goals and staying informed about our investments through the help of a financial advisor. No two retirement plans are alike, which is why it’s important to build a plan that’s right for YOU!

To enforce this even more, a recent study from @IGWealthManagement revealed one of the most common myths about retirement is that 63% of Canadians believe $1 million in savings is enough to retire on. This number may be right for some, but keep in mind that your retirement plan should be more than just investments, it should include things like lifestyle expenses, debt, health/life expectancy, inflation, estate goals and more.

Consider meeting with an @IGWealthManagement advisor to stay informed so that you can make decisions that are right for you, and successfully plan for the retirement lifestyle you've always dreamed of.

For more information, tune into the IG Wealth Management webinar “How to navigate today’s top five retirement challenges” on February 23rd at 2 PM EST. Link in bio! #Sponsored #IGWealthManagementPartner

You never think it’ll happen to you… until it does 💔 (TW)

Like I REALLY didn’t think it’d happen to me … at least this time around 💔 I held my breath during the super early weeks but I was really starting to become more confident and excited especially when my pants wouldn’t fit anymore.

It’s been a week since losing our new little bean and here are some things that have been in my mind this week:

🤍It doesn’t matter how early it happened. A miscarriage is devastating. At over 9 weeks, this little one had been my special little secret for 5 weeks. That’s over 35 days I anticipated you, loved you and dreamed of all you would be. I miss you like crazy and still can’t believe this is real.

🤍A miscarriage is physically painful but the emotional toll is worse. These cramps are intense and the expelling process is a traumatic blood-heavy scene but knowing that your body is rejecting the baby and the home it had been building made every trip to the bathroom a devastating experience. A physical reminder that my baby is gone.

🤍As I wrestle with God and ask the hard questions, I’m comforted by the fact that I can actually go to him freely with my grief and anger. He sees the heartbreak like no one else can and he comforts and heals like nothing else can. In Christ I can grieve with hope and look in anticipation at how he will make all things new.

I was overwhelmed with all your warm messages after sharing the news on my stories last week. Your thoughts, prayers amd stories honestly comforted me tremendously. Thank you for journeying with me. I’m not the influencer type - I’m not interesting or have a big personality or even like being in the spotlight frankly. But to have this platform to be heard, understood and related with mean the world to me ❤️

My new shopping obsession 🛍️

I have a strange relationship with shopping - so much so that it was a huge factor that affected my perception of my friendships and often led to me feeling left out growing up. I’ve never been a shopper. Back in the day, my girlfriends loved hanging out at the mall and window shopping. I couldn’t handle browsing anything for more than 10 minutes. Everyone loved talking about brands of clothes, shoes, and makeup. I probably couldn’t list 3 makeup brands. More often than not, you could beg me to go shopping and I’d much rather not. BUT I do get weird episodes of obsessive consumerism once in a while and splurge my heart out on the things I have on my mind. Lately it’s been flowers. Getting it all out of my system and moving on 😂
Adulting is hard 😂 so jealous that kids have such a carefree and fun outlook on life. Like and share if this is you every night!!
